{
  "stem": "1033.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And strangely enough, his name was also [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Vol, ?] but no relationship.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I remember, suddenly the door opened, and there was a young man throwing his arms and screaming.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And that was my grandmother's brother saying, George, come and run.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I took up and I went like a shot.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And then the following morning, that whole block was emptied.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But as I was running out, I remember this boy shouting after me, 'Tell my brother to get my ration.' Because in this place, we didn't get anything.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And that felt like, you know, what a rip off, because we were singled out for-- what do you call-- unusual punishment.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "But one [INAUDIBLE] I cannot understand that, or certainly find it hurts one's sense of justice or fairness.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "It's really ludicrous at this point for even-- to remember it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But nonetheless, these feelings were very real.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "After this incident, every night we could hear the guns in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we were hoping that the war would be over, but it wasn't.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And after this incident, the very first opportunity I managed to get, I got into a labor group.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "They were calling for people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Myself, and as I found later, three other kids got into this group.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And we were handed a bread, we were handed an overcoat with the back cut out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "It was a grey overcoat, a civilian coat, but the entire back was a big square was cut out with the letters K Z sewn in on a thin piece of cloth, which overcoat, incidentally, I had for many, many months, almost, until I was liberated in Dachau.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And we got on this train, and we ended up in a place called Kaufering.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "It was called [INAUDIBLE], Kaufering.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
